Policy-based VPNs are commonly used in simpler setups.

For example, a small business connects its office network to Azure using predefined IP ranges.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is branch offices accessing centralized resources in Azure.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is legacy firewall systems that only support policy-based VPN configurations.

These setups are straightforward but may not scale well for complex environments.
